caption: They offer a nice range of fresh food. I like dining here. Staff members are always super friendly, prices are convenient and the place is always clean.
So i got a refund but there was a maggot in my food. Im not really the type to make a big deal out of bugs but that means something in their kitchen is rotting...
Awesome khao soi and kee mao fried rice! I wouldn't order the spring rolls again but everything else tasted fresh and delicious. Will return!

This was our first time ordering delivery from Charm Thai, and we couldn't be happier! Everything was so great.  Ordering online was very easy and convenient Food arrived right at the scheduled time. Everything tasted good and just as we requested (e.g. spicy level). Price was very reasonable as well!  We were extremely happy and will make this more regular!  So happy to see a local restaurant do such a good job with everything, from food quality, to pricing, to customer service. Can't wait to support the restaurant more while enjoying delicious food.
I tried this spot once with a friend and I am addicted since then. I love the good atmosphere and fresh food and beverages. Highly recommended.

We were lucky enough to visit Thailand in November last year. Loved the food. This restaurant is so consistent with it's quality and taste!!! It's the best Thai food in the DMV hands down. The Khao Soi is amazing!!!!! So deep in layers of spices and flavor. Wow. You won't be disappointed getting a meal here.
The fall menu is amazing and chicken succulent.  They were able to make some things gluten free to accommodate my sensitivity.

I celebrated my PhD this evening in this great restaurant. I am glad to say that we enjoyed a astonishing evening and the venue was no doubt one of the reasons for that successful event. The stuff  contributed in a gorgeous style, the cuisine was great and my friends were so  pleased. We shall no dout visit again for more events. Thank you very much.

Delicious veggie pad thai, have ordered it multiple times over the past month! That said, their pad thai meat (version: chicken and steak) is perhaps over-cooked and the dumplings taste a bit off. Can't speak for the rest of the menu, but the veggie pad thai is great!
Very good spicy drunken noodles and yellow curry. However, please provide more napkins.
Best Pad Thai I’ve found in the area!
Surely a spot worth visiting, the food is awesome and well prepared, the pricing is convenient and it is constantly neat there. 5 stars.
This is my favorite Thai place, food is delicious!!

The food is good but the carryout packaging is terrible...  why does it seem like all Asian restaurants insist on using plastic?  Aren't there cardboard/aluminum alternatives?  It's not only the thick plastic black containers with clear lids (which are recyclable, but still), but also #6 clamshell, which I have to just throw away. So sad. Come on Charm Thai - can you find some better packaging??
The service is efficient and the food is very tasty and reasonable.
I tried this place already with my friend and I am addicted ever since. I like the good atmosphere and yummy food and drinks. Highly recommended.
Always good Thai

Ordered food for the first time with my family and it was worth it. They had the best pad see eaw I have ever tasted and it was so delicious. The wait time wasn't long and the employees were very respectful
Definitely one of the better restaurants in Silver Spring ! Same great taste every time.

Disappointed. I was so ready for the sweetness of crab in the crab fried rice, but the whole dish was overshadowed by the taste of black pepper, of which I'm not a fan. The fried chicken dumplings were okay, but I wouldn't return for them either. Sorry folks.

We've been ordering from Charm Thai for several years now and have always been so happy.  We usually order panang curry, mango and sticky rice, kee mao fried rice and pad see ew - we've had this for dinner so many times I can't even count! Their food is delicious and well-priced and the staff are great.  We've eaten in the restaurant many times, but have really appreciated their takeout safety changes through the pandemic.  Everything feels very safe and the food continues to be delicious.

I ordered veggie Kai soi soup among other things over Uber eats. I have ordered and dined in before and I have never had any problems. When the order arrived it had shrimp and chicken. I politely called and explained to them that I am a vegan and I do not eat meat. I asked for a new order to be delivered. The lady on the phone took 15min to understand and indicated that she will call back to confirm if they are even able fulfill my request. I agreed and waited. When I didn't hear from the woman after 20mins, I called to inquire about my order. She lied (yes, lied, because I was by my phone the entire time) and said she called me back. She then took my address and and then the order over again and had the audacity to say that the order will take 45 to 1hr. Not to mention I a live less that 4min away from the restaurant. ALSO, she say to me that i have to put the food that was delivered back into the container and return it back to them. By this point I am extremely irritated therefore I tell her never mind, I would like a refund and she proceeded to tell me that I need to call Uber eats to get my refund (which I understood). Then I ask for a manager and the woman continuously reiterated that I need to call Uber eats for a refund. I continuously explained that I understood but I still wanted to speak to some type of management. She refused to put management on the phone and eventually told me to call Thursday to speak with someone name Nom. VERY DISAPPOINTING!!!
The best food. The staff are incredible and quick with any orders.

We have tried quite a few Thai restaurants in Silver Spring/DC, but this is hands down our favorite. Their veggies are plentiful and varied (peppers, eggplant, onion, carrots, peas, etc.) in their curries, rather than just bamboo shoots. The Pad Thai and Drunken Noddle dishes are also fantastic. Highly recommend!
This spot is worth a try. They have large portions for convenient rates. Consistently well kept and with excellent character. I highly recommend this place.
This is the best kept secret in Silver Spring!
Best Thai food! I’ve been to Thailand and this is better that some of the food I’ve had over there. Great portions, fresh, and delicious! Delivered promptly.  You won’t go wrong ordering from here.
I always stop by purchasing some food here. I enjoyed the speedy customer service and well cooked dishes. Kudos.

Honestly, this is our go to for Thai. Amazing food. Always fresh. Great portions. Quick service. I would say this is a local Silver Spring favorite for a lot of people and for a good reason! Highly recommend.
The service is regularly efficient, great mood, helpful staff members. Will visit again when I get here.

I like to go with friends to this restaurant with my highest recommendations. I  go to this restaurant often. This recommendation is always successful. The the cooking is great and the crew is welcoming and cooperative. always when we eat in this place we have a delightful time.  warmly recommended.

Go here for the food and nothing else.  Service is spotty and rough which isn't relaxing or comforting. The woman who does to go with green contacts is rude and nasty.  She doesn't take responsibility for her staff or herself.
Nice little restaurant for lunch and dinner.

Soo good every time! Never disappoints! I’ve only rated take out from this restaurant, never dined in. The ambience of the actual restaurant is a bit lacking, so wouldn’t be my choice of place to dine in...but the food is on point! The Charm Thai Fried Rice is so flavorful. The KaoSoi is fantastic, spring rolls...shrimp cakes. All so good!
Good food!

It's a carryout with tables.  We came in January 2020 and the place was always cold because of the customer pick ups, and the comings and goings of the delivery staff. 2-3rds of the area is the narrow corridor. Even if there was good weather, it would be an uncomfortable and unsettling environment.  Food is pretty good and formulaic of the cultural cuisine but sweetened to the typical American diabetic-indusive taste, which subtracts from any sense of authenticity.  With the dinner so sweet, we had to skip dessert (and if you are diabetic, it'll  be wise for you too).  Even the plate of the hot food was cooled - nice for a salad, not for curry.  The small dining area and constant carryout customers taking priority over the diners, kills the ambiance, so this is not where I'd go to for a date again. And with only 4 parking spaces in front, makes pick up difficult.  Only my Shell Rewards brought me here.
I would call this American Thai food. It’s not authentic.
I have been coming here for the past 3 years and I love this place I have no complains the service was great the spicy eggplant tofu was amazing the portion was more than enough.
Food and service great
Very tasty.
Service and food was decent, tried drunken noodles and pad cashew. The quantity was lesser than other restaurants I have been too.

Very popular lunch spot! And for good reasons,  the food is great and the service is fast and friendly.   It can be a bit nois6but not enough to interrupt your conversation.  Most of the dishes are traditional and very authentic for American style Thai cuisine.  I was most surprised by the desert,  very traditional and very yummy.  If you haven't visited it's just off Georgia Avenue with plenty of convenient parking nearby.  Absolutely on my must visit again list.  Happy Eats
Very neat and accessible place. They serve generous portions and for affordable rates. I loved the menu a lot and the staff were very affable and informative. Will definitely recommend this spot.
I have the pad Thai it was good but short on the shrimps. I’ve tried other dishes and they where good too. There quality and the flavor 👍🏼 One star less because of the shrimp.

The food here is great and I've been a fan of everything I've tried. I usually order to go or have it delivered rather than dining in, but the restaurant itself seems to have a nice vibe when I've been waiting for my order. Of the appetizers, I like the curry puffs while my girlfriend lines the shrimp cakes. The girlfriend is much more habitual in her choice of entree, almost always getting the Pad Ka Pow with shrimp. On the other hand, I like switching it up and will usually choose between the Panang, Green and Massamun curries with either chicken or beef and the Nua Ka Ting (which is probably my single 'favorite' dish, although I like many).  Everything always tastes fresh and flavorful, the meat is always tender and juicy, and the high level of quality is extremely consistent. I can't remember having been disappointed even once. Getting extra rice with your entree is recommended, in my opinion, to absorb all the delicious sauce. Oh, and a Thai iced tea to wash it all down with is a good idea, too.  Cheers!
The food was overall good, although we felt rushed by the waitress.
Good food and excellent customer service

Cozy Thai spot with delicious and authentic offerings. We ordered the Tom Kha soup which was filled with coconut milk, lemongrass, cilantro, button mushrooms and chicken and we split a Chicken Pad Thai. The soup was both tangy and sweet which made for the perfect combination and the Pad Thai was pretty good, could have been a bit spicier and less soupy. The service was fine - patrons in the restaurant who sat down after us and ordered after us received their entrees before we did which was a bit frustrating but overall the experience was good. We’ll be back.
Really yummy Pad Thai!
Great Thai food, the khao soi is excellent.
Small and intimate setting but no complaints on the foot at all!
Charm Thai is our family favorite Thai restaurant. Great menu, great flavor, excellent value
Favorite thai restaurant in Silver Spring. So much flavor and perfect levels of spice. Favorites are: pad kee mao (drunken noodles), panang curry shrimp or beef, sticky rice and mango
The food was edible but the Pad Thai and the Pad See Ew more closely resembled Lo Mein than Thai food. Very disappointing give this place a miss

Food is good but dont ever order delivery directly from them.  Took almost an hour for .2 miles and it was missing part of the order.  Called and got hung up on twice and no apology for messing up.  Went to pick up the rest.  Also, ordered extra rice but there was none.
Larb gai and beef num tok (can be a bit spicy, but yummy) are delicious!  Also, can't go wrong with the fried tofu!
As the name states, charming little Thai place!
The food was amazing and the service here was so fast! The staff were also very friendly.
Food is excellent.
Delicious. Well priced. Great service.

I love the green curry, drunken noodles. The mixed veg with chicken/ tofu is a great option for kids.... Our picky 5 yr old loves it. Also we come all the way from Rockville for the mango, sticky rice and coconut icecream Sunday 🍨.
The food was delicious and the service was wonderful.
Like others have mentioned, Baldy is very rude. Food is overpriced and awful. Do not come here.
Consistently good food. Great lunch special also. Soup, drink, and entree for $13.
Panang Curry is amaaazing
Ordered for take out, food was really good.
Good fresh food, has gluten free options
Great food, timely, and friendly service, very fair price.
Very good Thai food and you can see it from how packed they are most of the time. Will keep returning.
Amazing food! Especially pad see Mao...I could eat every day!!!
The food was great! We especially loved the mangos chicken and the crispy duck.
Great delivery service and for fresh food! It's hard to find cellophane noodles so I'm happy!
Excellent that option in silver spring
The food was fine but have had much better Thai at other authentic spots. Still looking for a new spot here in Silver Spring that wows expectations.
I've only been there once for lunch, but I will definitely go back. I enjoyed the red curry chicken.
This restaurant is just a so so Meal size is so big size for me x But if you want to eat much? Then try it.

Authentic flavors at reasonable prices and good service make this a solid choice for a quick meal near downtown Silver Springs. Tables in the back are better as you dont get a blast of cold/hot air every time the door opens.  Parking is a pint to, but that's not something they control.

I love this place. They have a very affordable lunch menu. If you never tried Thai food before, this is an excellent place for 1st timers. Today I had the Drunken Noodles with chicken, chicken soup & Thai Coffee. Everything was delicious 😊

An excellent place to be a regular! (Fiancé and I are in almost every week).  The kitchen does all the standards just right—the lemongrass chicken has some good kick; the drunken noodles are spicy, springy and chewy; and the rainbow of curries has just the right amount of coconut milk (harder to get right than you think).  Order spicy, and wash it down with a bottled lager or a Thai iced tea.
Best Thai food in Silver Spring. Never disappointed, always satisfied, and the staff are great, too!
Excellent dumplings and a crispy fish salad. Friendly service.
The male bold head waitress was very rude and hyped it was our first time there he had no patience at all. We asked questions he didn't talk to us nice at all I won't be going back there again.
Great food and service!
Love this place

I love that this is a place I can get gluten free food. However I am often dissatisfied with the timeliness. When I order for carry out, they often take double the promised time to have it ready. The servers are kind when I ask how long it might be, but they seem to get yelled at by the chefs when asking about my order. It seems like a longer wait time or method of letting customers know the schedule is behind would be a nice addition to this process.
Best Thai food in the DMV area.
Cute enough place. Food was pretty good. Nothing super special but ok. I might try again.

This is probably my favorite Thai Restauarant, but not anymore. I was not aware that they put MSG in their foods and I react really badly with MSG. I wish that they would state that they do use MSG so that those that are allergic or just cannot handle MSG, would not face any consequences. It is the customers right to know what is in the food.
The food is delicious and the service is fantastic.
Great service.  Enjoyed the Panang and Thai Tea.
Just ok
Dehish..... Must try the Fried Brussel Sprouts
I’ve been searching for delicious creamy yellow curry and finally found the spot! This place is delicious!

The food was sublime and I have been eating at many Thai restaurants! Parking can be found behind the restaurant but spots are limited. Their menu offers variety of Thai food and all were great, especially the curry and pad Thai. The food didn’t take long to come out, and service was quick and super friendly!
Fast, flavorful thai good at a reasonable rate.
One of the few places I've found that make khao soi.
Best pad Thai I've had in the area! They do a lot of take out orders but it's also cute to sit and eat there.

Overall experience was average thus the rating of 3 out of 5 stars.  Walking in the staff was very attentive.  The place seems to have a nice atmosphere but my impression is that the bathroom came across as greasy and started to notice the worn tables and extremely dirty concrete floor with pieces of food everywhere.   Arrived at 5pm which meant I was receiving a dinner price which was $2 more for many items.  Ordered the pad thai which arrived very quickly but rice was an additional in cost too.  This seems like a staple for any Asian meal.  Was not asked for a thai spicy level but was given spice condiments to add to meal.  Overall was not asked for spicy level and felt very expensive for the amount of food provided.  Actually felt a little offended regarding when asking if I could get a side of rice and told that costs extra.  Their business model with all the window stickers and even sign on the street was for delivery.  Environment felt very confining with the wall between the kitchen and the front half of the dining area.  This place is in need of a makeover and prices to compete with the numerous thai places in the area.
Very good food and friendly service!
Good food! I like the atmosphere in the restaurant, but it is also super convenient for delivery via Uber eats
Food is horrible, not sure if it’s properly cooked. Service needs to be improved.  The waitress barely knows what she is doing.

I've been living in this area about a year and just discovered this place. The food is by far the most delicious I've had in this area and also a kind staff. I ordered delivery and missed the call the driver was here and they came back to drop of the food that was still hot even after I offered to come by to pick it up. My new spot for sure.
I've been eating here for a few months and I enjoy the food more and more every time I come here. The service is great and the food is the way I like it. Spicy.
Very good place and  very good tast
It's a good place to lunch, they have lunch specials and offer a vibrant atmosphere . The chefs are bona fide and the pac Thai I had was really good. Come and visit, they have good service too!
Great food, good service!
Went during lunch. Padthai w/ chicken was PERFECT. I also enjoyed the shrimp bikini as a starter.

I can here with a party of 6. The hostess was fairly inattentive. Also, she forgot to give utensils to half our party and we had to flag her down to get it for the rest of the table. My noodles were so chopped up it was like I was eating noodle mush. The dish also was under-seasoned. I'm comparison to other Thai restaurants in the area, the food at this restaurant is mediocre at best.
Great service. Great food. Highly recommend!
Tasty lunch at a great price.
The chicken Pad Mee is delicious! Probably the best Thai place I have found in the DMV. One takeout dinner lasts me for two meals and is reasonably priced.
Food was tasty and the staff are great. Good prices!
It was a really nice place food was good! Service was good and fast.
The food is always good. I recommend the pad ka prow and curry puffs.

Walked in for a sit down dinner. Patiently waited for 5-7 minutes. People in the place started looking at me wondering "Where is the hostess?"  I sat down at a table, and to the shock of people near me, ignored for another 5+ minutes. 10-12 minutes, no service. Finally someone looked my way, and she went back to whatever she was doing. At that point, I left. I won't be back. Worst service ever,
Drunken noodles were good but the Tom Yum soup had a lot of broth and very little substance.
Excellent little place! Loved it! Quick and polite service
As always, the place is welcoming and I love it.
Great lunch specials
Hurried by staff. Food ok but not that good. Curry puffs crust thick and doughy.
The food is amazing! It reminds me of Thailand!
Best thai food I've had in a long time, so consistently good. The pad thai is incredible.

Small place with a little awkward sitting. Service is fast except for delivery ( take-out fast as well). From menu I would suggest to go with seafood dishes. And yes's, they do serve wine and beer, but it's not on the menu - you should ask.

It pains me to write this review, because I don't want to share this awesome restaurant with ANYONE! It's a small place you're liable to walk past. But don't-- inside, they cook some of the best Thai food I've eaten outside of Thailand.  Prices are great-- a place where you can go, with your two boys who eat like horses, and not be worried that you'll have to dip into their college tuition savings to pay the bill. This place is really one of our favorites and has been for some time.

ordered the flank steak appitzer , Chewy and rubbery , wouldnt eat again from them , ordered the tom yum soup , cilantro looked old in soup , highly disapointed , was my first time and my last time . NAVI THAI IN WHEATON . Thai lemon grass in alexandrai va , hell ruby thai in the mall was better then charm thai . Thari thai in rockville is even better .
Love the chicken satay appetizer and the mixed vegetable and chicken dish. There is also really good service and the restaurant is super cute
Food is delicious but servers are rude.
Go to restaurant when I don't feel like cooking. They never disappoint!
One of the best food I ever had. You should try curry here.
They make it spicy when you really want it that way.

I came here to order pad thai with chicken to go. Flavor wise, I thought it was on point. The noodles were the same compared to others. They had a good balance of the remaining ingredients. I will come back and try something else and to truly get the experience of the restaurant. Until then, I would say this place is a 3.5 to 4 stars.  I was quite surprised that they would charge me 5 cents for the plastic bag. This would be the first restaurant that I've been to that has ever done so. Not sure how I feel about that.  The limited interaction with the staff was fine. Courteous and friendly.  Overall, I would recommend this place.
Excellent chicken fried rice! The Lunch special is a great offer... Try the sweet ice tea!
Yummy and reasonably priced
Great food and great people.
Friendly efficient staff. Good Thai food.
Great Thai food! The yellow curry was particularly awesome and delicious! I want that recipe!
Great place to go good was great
Pad Thai is to die for!
Great food
Quick service and reasonable prices with quality food.
Great Tai food. I highly recommend the red curry!
Reliably spicy Thai. We visit several times a month.

If you Love Thai & great service this is it! Drunken Noodles (Seafood) and Tom Yum Soup (Chicken with Mixed veggies lemongrass n chili paste base).  I've been coming here since they opened, nothing on the menu is honestly less than a home run!  10 people have entered within maybe 15 minutes @ 6:30pm on a rainy chilly Tuesday and countless orders going out for delivery.  (Including grub hub and Uber eats btw)
Decent drunken noodles.
Great green curry and a good price for lunch. The helping was enough for two!
Best Thai food in Silver Spring! Good atmosphere, friendly staff, and a good selection of drinks.
I like the service and the atmosphere is pretty good but the dishes don't change much in quality from order to order. Reliable
My favorite thai place in the DC area. Everything is great.
Tiny place with great Thai food
Great noodle dishes
Tried the Pad See Ew and the Crispy Salmon Panang. Both were great!
Good Thai food... I like the curries the most.

Decent Thai food in the middle of Silver Spring, Maryland. Lunch specials, awesome pineapple fried rice, and a seafood soup well worth the five bucks, despite the small size. Nice selection of curries, too. Friendly staff. Inexpensive public parking garage behind the building where the restaurant is located.
Great food to take out.  Place is very small  to eat
Best yellow chicken curry!
Friendly service . Nice and cheap Thai food and lunch specials of good value !!
We come back again and again. Lovely staff and delicious Thai food!
Although the restaurant is fairly small, the food was excellent & authentic. My father, who is an extremely picky eater, very much enjoyed this restaurant as well. Staff was also super friendly!

Nice Thai food for a good price. The panang curry with chicken was absolutely delicious!  I was on the fence about ordering it bc my experience with panang hasn't always been great.  While I like the combination of sweet and savory, most of the versions I've had have been cloyingly sweet and far too heavy.  Fortunately, I read few good reviews and decided to give it a shot.  So glad I did!  It definitely delivered the sweet and savory, but it was so much more.  There was a wonderful spiciness that I hadn't expected.  In addition to being incredibly flavorful, the sauce was the perfect consistency--not too thick/heavy but not too thin either.  I'll definitely go back to try more items on the menu.
Great lunch spot with good prices. Food is consistent and portions are large.
Does both carryout and in-restaurant service good.

Normally i ll order the panang chicken with white rice. Today i wanted something different so i order the pad Thai. I must admit it was pretty bad. i could barely take 3 bites because it was way to dry and plan for my taste..i was very disappointed .

This restaurant was great!  My kids loved the rice noodles with pork and pineapple fried rice.  My husband and I liked their dishes plus the chicken "birds nest" and the papaya red curry. Everything was very flavorful and spicy but not super hot which was fine for me.  The staff was very nice and if someone wanted the food hotter, I am sure they would accomodate.
Best Thai place in downtown Silver Spring
good food, good prices, only been for lunch and would go back again.

One of the many thai options in the area. The pad thai, pad see ew, and panang curry were all solid and portions were fair.  The panang curry was a little too thick but thats just my opinion, some may like it that way.  Seating was quick and service was pleasant.

worst thai food i've ever ordered, and that's saying something.  the pad thai was bland.  the tom kha tasted like it was made entirely out of fish sauce.  the panang looked like a red curry, and tasted nothing like panang.  their peanut sauce tastes like paste.  and, a single spring roll was 5 bucks. really?  it's rice paper and rice vermicelli.  why any person would order from this place is beyond me.

I love this place, their food is really good BUT today I pick-up Spicy Eggplant Lunch special while its raining crazy.  The packed serving portion is just way too small, not enough for even light lunch....and when I say not enough is I eat very less compare to rest of the gang and I normally have some leftover from my lunch specials after I finish my lunch.  This is not worth spending your money if you can't even get decent lunch amount serving packed when ordered :(  I am really upset at the moment.  I work around the block from this place and I am not going to pick-up lunch here again!
Best Thai food I've had in the entire DC area. It's just unfortunate that one has to travel out of DC to get it.

We ordered Panang Curry, Drunken Noodles and Kee Mao Fried Rice and all the dishes were delicious. The server was nice and courteous and the price was affordable. The only thing they could improve is the ambience.

The server was nice, but the food was less than satisying.  I ordered Pad Thai with shrimp and was charged extra for wanting it spicy.  I wound up paying  $14 for a huge plate of greasy noodles with 4 shrimp.  I've definitely gotten more bang for my buck elsewhere.  Will stick to my regular Thai restaurants in DC.  Very unsatisfied.
The food is decent, but sometimes inconsistent.  Sometimes "spicy" is bland, other times it is inedible.  They have a lot of vegetarian options.
Closest thing to downtown Bangkok in this town; best in August when it's hot & your clothes stick to you - it's all good, but start with the Drunken Noodles.
Great Thai Restaurant! Hard to find parking because of location, but great food!!!
I have been dining it  on regular basis but the food quality , taste and their quantity have gone down by almost 30% but not the price.

I went there today for the first time. I had the green curry. It was delicious. Also, we ordered the vegetable rolls as an appetizer and they were good. The two people I went with had drunken noodle and spicy eggplant. Both delicious as well. All vegetables looked fresh, cooked right, good amount of spice. Service was excellent. I would go there again.
This is the best Thai food in the DC area. I have yet to order something I didn't love. The Pa Ra Rom Song in particular is great.
Green curry was spicy and temperature hot,  very delicious. With a side of white rice it  was sufficient for lunch. I would like to try their special set lunch next time.

I really wanted to like this place. Went in there on a Monday night for take-out and ordered tom kha soup and pad thai w shrimp -- a pretty basic order that will tell me everything I need to know about a Thai restaurant. I should have known something was wrong when I smelled something smokey as I was driving home. It was coming from the takeout bag. Now nothing was actually burned, but there was a distinct burned oder coming off the pad thai. That wasn't the worst of it. The noodles were all shredded and congealed, as if these were pad thai leftovers that someone had then try to refry. Shrimp were overdone and tough. I could have done better myself with one of those packets from the store. Overall flavor was blah. The soup was not much better. Overly sweet. It also had tomatoes in it, which I did not care for. I won't be back and will be warning my friends.

Spicy! Yesssssss! I'm from out west and LOVE spicy food but people in this area are such wimps when it comes to spicy food that even when you ORDER spicy, it's still not spicy.  Not true with Charm Thai! I've had things that light MY hair on fire. I dare you to order something with the two stars marked as "extra spicy" and then TELL them "extra spicy" when you order it. Woohoo!  My favorite thing is just the regular chicken drunken noodles. The regular level of "extra spicy" that they come is just perfect. And TASTY spicy, too, not just spicy for spicy's sake.  I just discovered this place a couple months ago and had a few delivery orders. I think this is going to be my main take-out/delivery place now.
Great food, great Decor and Great service. Get a thai iced tea and drunken noodles. Be sure to ask them to make it very mild!
Food is great. The waiters are awesome. I love Charm Thai restuarant.

First visit just now for lunch. Veggies tasted fresh and weren't overcooked, service was friendly and timed nicely... even the iced tea was just right. It's a block from both my wife's office and my own -- we will be back regularly.
